                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Buffalo</placeName>\n                <add>?</add>\n                <date>17 <add>Hebrew</add> 5614</date>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <add>Hebrew</add>\n            </p>\n            <p>Revd</p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Sir!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Your Book, with the Books<lb/> I recd from <persName>Mr. E. J.\n                    Bernheim</persName>, and paid<lb/> the freight for on it, and also the\n                carriage,<lb/> only, I can't make you <sic>aquinted</sic> how<lb/> it will be, with\n                the delivery, this moment<lb/> when I write to you, I have said<add>?</add> to\n                    <persName>E. J.<lb/> Bernheim</persName>, if he want <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >one</hi>, but he did<lb/> not answer, no doubt you know the<lb/> nature of\n                those <add>?</add>, as they are<lb/> a <add>Hebrew</add>. I can not keep\n                    <add>?</add> any longer,<lb/> as I have, so much writing, and dis,<lb/>pute in\n                your Occident, on account<lb/> of <persName>Dr. Wises</persName> writing and in particular<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr Revd Dr Illowy</persName> how D<add>?</add> him! let<lb/> me stop, all\n                those disputes, I have a<lb/> valuable Book printed, by a great\n                <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> calld, <add>Hebrew</add>, and <persName>Mr Lane</persName>\n                writes only a few<lb/> words, <sic>wich</sic> will make <sic>betwen</sic> those\n                two<lb/> D<hi rend=\"underline\">rs</hi>. And he <sic>explain</sic> himself, with a\n                for<lb/>wards <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> 86<lb/>\n                <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> 86 and according all <add>Hebrew</add> upon our\n                    <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> the whole creation, <del>was</del> came in existence\n                    <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> and no doubt, every learned man knows,<lb/> that\n                    <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> at present I have but 2 scholars, the children,<lb/> of\n                    <persName>Mr <add>?</add> Noah</persName>, but in <add>?</add> of time I\n                may<lb/> let come some more as I keep school only<lb/> for a pass time.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p36h4db00/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
